Ashlee Brent, Lila Trevathan, Halle Trevathan, Josey Clark, McCall Sims, Lakyn Rogers, Sarah
Byars, Alexis Evans, Cambry Hatler, Carson Gibson, Amayiah Reed, Annelise Hayden, and
Anna Holmes Hurns; and
WHEREAS, Westview's superb performance would not have been possible without
Head Coach Brian Haskins, who has expertly guided the program for eleven years, and his
assistant coaches, Lauren Freeman, Randy Moore, Burton Rutledge, Jacey Sims, and Mike
Swaim, and the unfailing support of the players' families, their fans, and their close-knit
community; and
WHEREAS, the members of the Westview girls' basketball team epitomize all that is
good in today's student athletes, as they have achieved a premier level of success in
competition while exhibiting the highest degree of character in all aspects of life; and
WHEREAS, the perseverance, determination, work ethic, and talent of this group of
young women not only made possible a championship season but also surely bode well for their
future success; and
WHEREAS, the members of this General Assembly find it appropriate to acknowledge
and applaud the Westview Lady Chargers for their outstanding season on the hardwood; now,
therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE OF THE ONE HUNDRED FOURTEENTH
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE HOUSE OF
REPRESENTATIVES CONCURRING, that we honor and commend the members of the
Westview Lady Chargers girls' basketball team upon winning the 2025 TSSAA Division I, Class
2A state tournament, applaud their seven consecutive victories to claim their third state
championship in four years, and extend to them our best wishes for every continued success in
all their future endeavors.
